This is boring now.

1035
00:52:18,019 --> 00:52:21,940
The books continue to filter in and then slowly begin to stop.

1036
00:52:21,940 --> 00:52:24,260
And as he's quickly scanning through them,

1037
00:52:24,260 --> 00:52:26,019
he reaches the last book and he says,

1038
00:52:27,460 --> 00:52:31,539
Well, I feel like that's all I need to know.

1039
00:52:34,260 --> 00:52:38,019
And he puts the book down and then stands there for a moment.

1040
00:52:38,019 --> 00:52:41,059
And nothing happens.

1041
00:52:42,420 --> 00:52:42,920
No.

1042
00:52:45,460 --> 00:52:48,099
Well, how about you two come with me

1043
00:52:48,099 --> 00:52:49,539
and we've got to go find more to learn.

1044
00:52:50,659 --> 00:52:51,380
More to learn?

1045
00:52:52,500 --> 00:52:53,699
Yeah, well, we haven't learned at all.

1046
00:52:53,699 --> 00:52:54,420
Look at all these books.

1047
00:52:54,420 --> 00:52:56,099
There's still apparently something to know.

1048
00:52:56,099 --> 00:52:58,179
Do we have to go back up and get more books?

1049
00:52:59,300 --> 00:53:00,420
Well, this should be all the books.

1050
00:53:00,420 --> 00:53:02,340
I told them all to come follow down behind us.

1051
00:53:03,219 --> 00:53:06,739
Well, wait, let's, well, okay, now hold on a second.

1052
00:53:06,740 --> 00:53:09,460
Are you going to like secure them in here

1053
00:53:09,460 --> 00:53:12,900
so that your angry wizards don't get them?

1054
00:53:12,900 --> 00:53:14,420
What about that book that you wrote?

1055
00:53:15,300 --> 00:53:16,420
Do you have a copy of that?

1056
00:53:17,220 --> 00:53:18,180
You wrote a book?

1057
00:53:18,180 --> 00:53:19,860
I did not write a book.

1058
00:53:19,860 --> 00:53:21,780
Well, he orated it, right?

1059
00:53:21,780 --> 00:53:22,280
Yes.

1060
00:53:23,060 --> 00:53:28,660
I gave a few ideas to someone else who was writing a book.

1061
00:53:28,660 --> 00:53:29,460
Really?

1062
00:53:29,460 --> 00:53:29,940
Yeah.

1063
00:53:29,940 --> 00:53:30,980
What was your book about?

1064
00:53:31,860 --> 00:53:33,540
Uh, Gross Jobs.

1065
00:53:33,539 --> 00:53:36,980
Interest me.

1066
00:53:36,980 --> 00:53:39,380
I just listed Gross Jobs.

1067
00:53:39,380 --> 00:53:42,340
Walk with me and tell me about all of your gross jobs.

1068
00:53:42,340 --> 00:53:45,860
Okay, so I already mentioned Banya Masebeta.

1069
00:53:45,860 --> 00:53:47,300
As your list continues on,

1070
00:53:47,300 --> 00:53:49,380
the three of you walk back out of the cavern

1071
00:53:49,380 --> 00:53:52,739
and he, like, with a swipe of his hand,

1072
00:53:52,739 --> 00:53:56,259
the dirt begins to mold back around the room,

1073
00:53:56,820 --> 00:53:59,380
so securing the books inside.

1074
00:53:59,380 --> 00:54:02,340
You begin to head back upstairs where we cut back to Glim,

1075
00:54:02,420 --> 00:54:05,460
who's speaking with Grandpa Big Dog and Kath Silverson.

1076
00:54:05,460 --> 00:54:07,539
He's like, look, we just need to get past you.

1077
00:54:07,539 --> 00:54:08,820
Do I hear that at all?

1078
00:54:08,820 --> 00:54:11,140
I do have the door slightly ajar behind me.

1079
00:54:11,140 --> 00:54:13,620
This, like, chamber closing in on itself?

1080
00:54:15,140 --> 00:54:17,220
They were down the tunnel.

1081
00:54:17,220 --> 00:54:17,860
Down the tunnel.

1082
00:54:17,860 --> 00:54:19,300
They're walking back up the tunnel now.

1083
00:54:20,340 --> 00:54:22,980
You've heard less movement of books.

1084
00:54:22,980 --> 00:54:26,900
Like, you could hear, like, the books dancing across the room,

1085
00:54:27,460 --> 00:54:28,740
but now less movement of that.

1086
00:54:28,740 --> 00:54:30,579
And he's like, look, we just need to get past you.

1087
00:54:31,460 --> 00:54:32,819
Yeah, I'm not going to let you pass me.

1088
00:54:32,819 --> 00:54:33,299
Hold on.

1089
00:54:33,299 --> 00:54:35,299
Oh, we can take care of the Mesecs.

1090
00:54:37,219 --> 00:54:38,659
And are the books all gone now?

1091
00:54:38,659 --> 00:54:40,019
The books are all gone.

1092
00:54:40,019 --> 00:54:40,519
OK.

1093
00:54:42,900 --> 00:54:44,500
Do I see or hear them yet?

1094
00:54:45,139 --> 00:54:50,819
You hear low muffled noise, the sound of Sully.

1095
00:54:50,819 --> 00:54:52,500
So they're, like, a ways away still.

1096
00:54:52,500 --> 00:54:53,059
Yeah.

1097
00:54:53,059 --> 00:54:54,819
OK, I'm going to open the door again.

1098
00:54:54,819 --> 00:54:56,579
What do you mean you're going to take care of the Mesecs?

1099
00:54:56,579 --> 00:54:58,259
What are you going to do to the Mesecs?

1100
00:54:59,220 --> 00:55:02,980
As you open back the door, you see that Grandpa Big Dog's hand

1101
00:55:02,980 --> 00:55:06,260
is on something, and he kind of sneaks it back into his robe.

1102
00:55:06,260 --> 00:55:09,380
And he's like, we're going to get rid of the Mesecs

1103
00:55:09,380 --> 00:55:11,140
before he learns absolutely everything

1104
00:55:11,140 --> 00:55:13,780
and can rule the world before he learns.

1105
00:55:13,780 --> 00:55:15,780
OK, we're going to stop the Mesecs

1106
00:55:15,780 --> 00:55:17,460
before he almost learns everything

1107
00:55:17,460 --> 00:55:19,780
and then can rule the world trying to know everything.

1108
00:55:20,900 --> 00:55:22,980
But if he knows everything, won't he just, like,

1109
00:55:22,980 --> 00:55:25,460
disappear like that other one did when he picked up the rock?

1110
00:55:25,460 --> 00:55:28,260
Yeah, but it's what happens as he's trying to achieve that.

1111
00:55:31,300 --> 00:55:32,420
What do you got in your pocket there?

1112
00:55:34,659 --> 00:55:35,940
Mesecs box.

1113
00:55:41,059 --> 00:55:41,860
What does that mean?

1114
00:55:42,740 --> 00:55:43,619
So you're not going to kill him?

1115
00:55:43,619 --> 00:55:45,059
You're just going to put him in a box?

1116
00:55:45,059 --> 00:55:46,500
I mean, that's eventually where they go,

1117
00:55:46,500 --> 00:55:48,099
is they go back into the Mesecs box.

1118
00:55:52,099 --> 00:55:53,699
And it's not going to hurt him.

1119
00:55:56,019 --> 00:55:57,220
I mean, can a Mesecs feel?

1120
00:55:58,340 --> 00:56:00,420
I didn't even know a Mesecs was a thing.

1121
00:56:00,420 --> 00:56:01,539
This is very interesting.

1122
00:56:02,260 --> 00:56:03,059
Yes, yes.

1123
00:56:03,860 --> 00:56:05,460
So Mesecs don't feel anything.

1124
00:56:06,019 --> 00:56:06,579
I forgot.

1125
00:56:06,579 --> 00:56:07,539
I should have led with that.

1126
00:56:08,659 --> 00:56:12,579
Mesecs, they're here one minute, they're gone the next.

1127
00:56:13,780 --> 00:56:16,980
And that's all you need to know.

1128
00:56:16,980 --> 00:56:19,860
And we're just here to clean up the mess of somebody else.

1129
00:56:20,420 --> 00:56:21,699
OK, I'll be back in a second.

1130
00:56:21,699 --> 00:56:23,940
I'm going to go back inside and close the door.

1131
00:56:25,460 --> 00:56:26,420
And open the door again.

1132
00:56:26,420 --> 00:56:27,699
Can you guys keep it down out here?

1133
00:56:27,699 --> 00:56:29,380
I'm trying to work out a situation.

1134
00:56:29,380 --> 00:56:30,900
Maybe like stay a bit hidden or something.

1135
00:56:31,940 --> 00:56:32,420
What?

1136
00:56:34,740 --> 00:56:35,220
OK.

1137
00:56:38,179 --> 00:56:39,139
Master Mesecs?

1138
00:56:40,900 --> 00:56:43,139
So you have to put your finger where?

1139
00:56:44,260 --> 00:56:45,300
Oh, yeah.

1140
00:56:45,300 --> 00:56:48,099
So like right up there and push the hemorrhoids.

1141
00:56:48,980 --> 00:56:49,380
Oh, hey.

1142
00:56:50,340 --> 00:56:50,659
Hi.

1143
00:56:51,619 --> 00:56:52,019
Yeah.

1144
00:56:52,019 --> 00:56:54,019
Looks like you got all your books moved.

1145
00:56:54,579 --> 00:56:54,980
I did.

1146
00:56:54,980 --> 00:56:58,340
I was just learning some very interesting things from your friend here.

1147
00:56:58,340 --> 00:56:59,460
I bet you were.

1148
00:56:59,460 --> 00:57:02,019
Sully does know all the most interesting things.

1149
00:57:02,579 --> 00:57:05,699
I mean, he told me 99 jobs out of 100 job book.

1150
00:57:05,699 --> 00:57:06,820
What was the last job?

1151
00:57:08,980 --> 00:57:10,420
Oh, a bitch ain't one.

1152
00:57:12,019 --> 00:57:12,340
Oh.

1153
00:57:12,340 --> 00:57:30,820
Oh, you see him kind of stop and puzzled as he kind of you see his eyes roll back

1154
00:57:30,820 --> 00:57:34,740
into his head as his hands move up.

1155
00:57:34,740 --> 00:57:37,539
And it's almost like he's trying to count, but he has mitten hands.

1156
00:57:37,539 --> 00:57:41,460
So it's like he's counting one.

1157
00:57:41,460 --> 00:57:46,500
Just one, one, one, one, one, one, one, one, one, one, one, zero, one, one.

1158
00:57:46,500 --> 00:57:52,099
And then he pops out of existence and his robes drop to the ground.

1159
00:57:52,980 --> 00:57:55,059
Oh, God, I broke Mr. Mesecs.

1160
00:57:55,699 --> 00:57:56,659
Sully, what did you do?

1161
00:57:57,300 --> 00:58:00,099
Well, guys, I think.

1162
00:58:01,380 --> 00:58:02,260
Sully, I think.

1163
00:58:03,940 --> 00:58:05,860
I think you saved the day.

1164
00:58:07,619 --> 00:58:07,860
What?

1165
00:58:07,860 --> 00:58:09,139
No, that doesn't sound like me.

1166
00:58:09,139 --> 00:58:10,500
From the list of jobs?

1167
00:58:12,099 --> 00:58:16,500
I just finished telling him about how to put hemorrhoids back into a person.

1168
00:58:16,500 --> 00:58:20,659
I'm not entirely sure that that is anywhere on par with saving a day.

1169
00:58:22,019 --> 00:58:22,659
Well.

1170
00:58:22,659 --> 00:58:25,780
Unless you're that person who's getting those hemorrhoids pushed back in,

1171
00:58:25,780 --> 00:58:26,579
because let me tell you.

1172
00:58:27,460 --> 00:58:28,820
I'll explain everything, but.

1173
00:58:29,860 --> 00:58:30,740
And I opened the door.

1174
00:58:32,019 --> 00:58:32,740
Did we come in yet?

1175
00:58:32,740 --> 00:58:33,699
Are the guys still there?

1176
00:58:33,699 --> 00:58:34,980
Yeah, oh yeah, we're still here.

1177
00:58:35,780 --> 00:58:36,740
Well, great news.

1178
00:58:37,460 --> 00:58:38,260
Great news.

1179
00:58:38,260 --> 00:58:38,760
Good.

1180
00:58:39,780 --> 00:58:40,980
He disappeared.

1181
00:58:40,980 --> 00:58:42,260
Yeah, I destroyed the blue guy.

1182
00:58:44,260 --> 00:58:48,740
Are you sure he disappeared or didn't learn to teleport and is now just somewhere else?

1183
00:58:49,619 --> 00:58:51,380
Well, how could I possibly know that?

1184
00:58:52,260 --> 00:58:53,460
Can I come in?

1185
00:58:53,460 --> 00:58:55,860
Well, his robes fell to the floor.

1186
00:58:55,860 --> 00:58:58,900
Wouldn't a teleporting person take their clothes with them?

1187
00:59:00,820 --> 00:59:06,579
Look, sometimes with teleportation or time travel or anything like that,

1188
00:59:06,579 --> 00:59:08,340
sometimes your clothes can't go with you.

1189
00:59:08,340 --> 00:59:12,500
But if you let me come in, I can do a quick test and then we'll be done.

1190
00:59:13,220 --> 00:59:16,180
Okay, well, grandpa big dog.

1191
00:59:16,180 --> 00:59:17,059
That's me.

1192
00:59:17,059 --> 00:59:17,940
Grandpa big dog.

1193
00:59:17,940 --> 00:59:19,460
Bad ass name, my man.

1194
00:59:19,460 --> 00:59:20,340
Bad ass name.

1195
00:59:21,140 --> 00:59:21,380
Hey, don't make-

